[SN]TITLE[SN]
Wall Street rises as oil price edges higher

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
(Open): Wall Street opened sharply higher on Tuesday as oil prices recovered from Monday's falls.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The main Dow Jones index was up 168.33 points, or 1%, at 17,696.60. The wider S&P 500 was 0.8% higher, while the tech-heavy Nasdaq climbed 0.7%.
Both Brent and US light crude were up 84 cents, or 2.3%, a barrel.
Following the slight recovery in the oil price, energy stocks rose, with Chevron up 1.1% and Exxon Mobil 0.6% higher.
The price of Brent oil is currently $37.46, while US light crude is trading at $37.65.
In the run-up to Christmas, Brent sank to $36.04, its lowest level since July 2004.
Away from the energy sector, chemicals giant DuPont led the way on the Dow, rising 1.7%.
No stocks on the index lost ground.
